Just be aware that doing this will call `Dosomething` on every MonoBehaviour on that gameobject.


If you want to be specific about which `MonoBehaviour` to call on and/or have the references to the `MonoBehaviour`s specifically, you can use [`MonoBehaviour.Invoke`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/MonoBehaviour.Invoke.html):

