`() -&gt;` is a lambda that accepts no parameters as opposed to something like `(a,b,c) -&gt;` which accepts three parameters.

The parameters can also have types: `(int a, long b, Object c) -&gt; `

The code `() -&gt; create(Invalid_Name)` is saying &quot;a function that calls `create(Invalid_Name)`.

